Uses IBM Watson Add-on to transcribe conference call, voice call with Twilio. Simple implementation from https://www.twilio.com/docs/add-ons/tutorials/how-to-use-recordings-add-ons-in-nodejs.

Twilio Configuration - 
Your /voice URL can be the incoming voice webhook on your purchased twilio number. That will make this number a simple recording machine with transcription service.
The /conf URL can be the incoming voice webhook on your purchased number. That will make this number a conference line with automatic transcription service.
The /callback URL will be the Watson Callback URL on your Watson Add-on: https://www.twilio.com/console/add-ons/XB85b56ed9ce713e0ac62342b901233193

You can also access your recordings in your Twilio console.

File options -
1) Download to a .txt file locally (useWatsonAddon.js)
2) Write to a Google Sheet (index.js)
   Follow this: https://www.twilio.com/blog/2017/02/an-easy-way-to-read-and-write-to-a-google-spreadsheet-in-python.html
   Initialize by sharing the email in your client_secret.json with the spreadsheet of editing access.
   Change the spread sheet ID to yours.


